token. Store\nthat in your safe-keeping for this project."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h1","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Deploy the Stack"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Then, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://console.aws.amazon.com/cloudformation/home?region=us-east-1#/stacks/new?stackName=github-sheets-sync&templateURL=https://sammarks-cf-templates.s3.amazonaws.com/github-sheets-sync/template.yaml","target":"_blank","rel":["noopener"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"click here to launch the\nstack."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\nYou can also review the options over at the Github repository."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"github","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"sammarks/objection-graphql-relay"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Once you click that link, you’ll be taken to the AWS Console where you might be asked to verify your\ncredentials. Once you login, you’ll be taken to the “Create Stack” screen inside CloudFormation. All\nof the stuff in the first step is filled out nicely for you, so just go ahead and hit "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Next"}]},{"type":"text","value":" at\nthe bottom."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Give your stack a creative name! Our very creative example is "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"github-sheets-sync"}]},{"type":"text","value":", see if you can\ncome up with something better."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Now for the parameters. Let’s start with the most important ones, and then we’ll move into\ncustomizing the rest if your heart desires. Get out your Github token that you generated in the last\nsection, and put that in the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"GithubToken"}]},{"type":"text","value":" field."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Then, paste the email address you copied from the service account section into the\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"GoogleClientEmail"}]},{"type":"text","value":" field. Now take the private key you copied, wrap it in quotes, and put it in\nthe "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"GooglePrivateKey"}]},{"type":"text","value":" field. The result should look something like this: "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\"-----BEGIN PRIVATE\nKEY-----\\nabddfd...\""}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Quotes are important!"}]},{"type":"text","value":" It’s pretty important that you add the quotes, so we can make sure Amazon\ndoesn’t fiddle with our private key. If you don’t include the quotes, the whole thing is pretty much\nguaranteed to not work."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Inside the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"SpreadsheetId"}]},{"type":"text","value":" field, paste the spreadsheet ID you copied way back at the very\nbeginning of this article. Inside the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"SheetName"}]},{"type":"text","value":" field, type in the name of the sheet you want\nthe Github issues to be inserted into."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Finally, inside the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Repository"}]},{"type":"text","value":" field, type in the name of the repository you want to sync, in\nthe format of "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"owner/repository"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You’ll need to deploy the stack multiple times to sync multiple repositories."}]},{"type":"text","value":" I know, I’ll get\naround to it. If you want to do my work for me, you can submit a PR!"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h1","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Customizing"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you’re an eager beaver and want to jump straight into syncing your fancy issues, feel free to\nskip over this part. By default, the stack syncs all issues with the “reporting” label, and syncs\nboth open and closed issues. It also syncs every 30 minutes, Monday - Friday, during reasonable(ish)\ndaytime hours."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you want to change the cron specification for how often to sync, update the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"UpdateSchedule"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\nfield. This field accepts a "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonCloudWatch/latest/events/ScheduledEvents.html","target":"_blank","rel":["noopener"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"CloudWatch\nScheduleExpression,"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\nso if you wanted to sync every hour, 24/7, you would put in something like this: "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"rate(1 hour)"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you only want to sync open issues, just change "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"State"}]},{"type":"text","value":" from “OPEN,CLOSED” to just “OPEN”"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you want to sync with a label other than “reporting,” just update the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Labels"}]},{"type":"text","value":" field."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h1","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Finish and Test"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Once you’re done making all of your customizations, hit the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Next"}]},{"type":"text","value":" button at the bottom. Nothing\nis really relevant to us on the next screen, so just hit "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Next"}]},{"type":"text","value":" again. Then scroll wayyyy to the\nbottom, check all of the checkboxes inside the blue box (this is just to make sure you know what\nyou’re doing, and that this stack assigns some permissions to itself to be able to run, etc). Then\nhit "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Create Stack."}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Then you’re taken to your stack screen, so now you get to watch and hope the cogs at AWS are\nturning! Wait until the stack is created, and then we’re done. At this point, you could just wait\nyour 30 minutes or whatever time interval you’ve configured and check the Google Sheet to make sure\nthe issues are synced, but if you’re impatient and want to test manually, keep going."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Head over to "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Lambda"}]},{"type":"text","value":" using the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Services"}]},{"type":"text","value":" dropdown at the top. Find the Lambda function our\nfancy stack just created. It should be called something like "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"github-sheets-sync-xxxx"}]},{"type":"text","value":". Give it a\nclick."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"At the top-right corner of the page, there is a dropdown and a button called "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Test."}]},{"type":"text","value":" Click on the\ndropdown, and then click "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Configure test events."}]},{"type":"text","value":" Make sure "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Create new test event"}]},{"type":"text","value":" is selected\ntoward the top of the screen, and then fill out something creatively random for the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Event name"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\nfield. For our creatively random name, we chose “test.” No need to pay attention to the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Event\ntemplate"}]},{"type":"text","value":" field, it has no use for us."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Click "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Create"}]},{"type":"text","value":" at the bottom of the dialog, and then hit that "},{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Test"}]},{"type":"text","value":" button. A panel will pop up\nsaying your magical function is currently running, and then should hopefully turn green. Then check\nyour spreadsheet, and your issues should be there!"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you run into some issues, head back to the CloudFormation service and check the values you\nentered inside the stack to make sure they’re correct. Otherwise, "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://github.com/sammarks/cloudformation-github-sheets-sync/issues","target":"_blank","rel":["noopener"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"check the issue\nqueue"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and see if someone else\nhas had the same problem."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"className":["custom-block","block-success"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"className":["custom-block-heading"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"icon-success","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You’ve done it!"}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{"className":["custom-block-body"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Lambda function you’ve deployed will continue to run during business hours (you can update\nthe configuration inside the AWS console), syncing your Github issues with the Google sheet. Hand\nthat over to your ops team and go get yourself a much-needed celebratory snack."}]}]}]}],"data":{"quirksMode":false}},"fields":{"slug":"/posts/automatically-syncing-github-issues-google-sheets/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Automatically syncing Github issues with Google Sheets"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/automatically-syncing-github-issues-google-sheets/"}}}